{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} In art, a '''dedication''' is the creation or attribution of a work of art as a [[tribute]] to or in honor of a person, place, or thing. The dedicatee may be the [[commission (art)|commissioner]], conductor, premiere performer or musical ensemble, or patron. The work may be [[memorial]].
In music, examples include many of [[Ludwig van Beethoven|Beethoven]]'s works, such as the [[Piano Sonata No. 30 (Beethoven)|Piano Sonata Op. 109]], dedicated to his friend [[Antonie Brentano]]'s daughter Maximiliane.<ref name="Anderson2007">{{cite AV media notes|url=http://www.naxos.com/mainsite/blurbs_reviews.asp?item_code=8.557724&catNum=557724&filetype=About%20this%20Recording&language=English#|last=Anderson|first=Keith|title=Beethoven: Piano Trios, Vol. 2 – Piano Trios Nos. 1, 2, 9|publisher=[[Naxos Records]]|type=CD|ID=8.572343|year=2007|ref={{harvid|Anderson|2007}}}}</ref><ref name="CooperP225">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=Tq5ci-9OMLEC|title=Beethoven|last=Cooper|first=Barry|authorlink=Barry Cooper (musicologist)|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=United States|year=2000|isbn=978-0191592706|page=225|ref={{harvid|Cooper|2000}}}}</ref>
In literature, examples include [[Vladimir Nabokov]]'s dedication of works to his wife [[Véra Nabokov|Véra]].
