{{Infobox artwork | title = Salmon Gargoyle | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | image = Salmon_Gargoyle_(1987)_by_Wayne_Chabre,_Eugene,_Oregon.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = The sculpture in October 2015 | artist = [[Wayne Chabre]] | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1987}} | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | type = Sculpture | material = Copper, stainless steel | subject = Salmon | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | height_imperial = 5 | width_imperial = 3 | length_imperial = 8.5 | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = m <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = ft <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = "Treatment needed" (1993) | city = [[Eugene, Oregon]], United States | museum = | accession = | coordinates = {{coord|44.04296|-123.06842|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = University of Oregon Campus | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location on the University of Oregon campus | pushpin_label_position = | owner = [[University of Oregon]] | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''''Salmon Gargoyle''''' is an outdoor 1987 sculpture by [[Wayne Chabre]], installed in 1988 on the [[University of Oregon]] campus in [[Eugene, Oregon]], in the United States. The hammered copper head of a salmon with Kwakiutl Indian representation on its sides, built on a stainless steel frame, measures approximately {{Convert|5|ft|m}} x {{Convert|3|ft|m}} x {{Convert|8.5|ft|m}}. It was surveyed and deemed "treatment needed" by the [[Smithsonian Institution]]'s "[[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]]" program in March 1993. The sculpture is administered by the University of Oregon.<ref name=SI>{{cite web|title=Salmon Gargoyle, (sculpture).|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!310861~!0#focus|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]|accessdate=January 24, 2016}}</ref>
